                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.4016/60: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-08T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 8, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 8—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>228. My telegram No. 187, July 29, noon and my telegram No. 207, August 19, 6
                    p.m. We have informally requested information concerning various aspects of
                    recent anti-Semitic decrees as applicable to American citizens but have thus far
                    succeeded only in obtaining confirmation of assurances reported in my No. 207,
                    August 19.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
